      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "Score another for Mayor Pratt's\ncourt of all nations and all causes.\nToday G. w. Ross and e. Craggs\nappeared with a grievance against\nthe Hanson employment agency.\nThey had each invested $40 in\ngetting jobs on assurance that no\nblankets were required. They dis\ncovered that individual blankets\nwere an element of holding the\njob when they got to it, and came\nback with a written statement 10\nthat effect.\n\n\nThe mayor summoned the en-\nployment agent, he admitted the\ncharge and the mayor suggested\nthat a refund was proper pro-\ncedure for the employment agent.\nThe suggestion was sufficient."
    }
